    "mplot1(Pred_grid_xy, spred_trans, rows, cols, title='Simple kriging', hillshade=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1a833d0f-2633-4fb2-ae31-f15ffe415028",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "The downside of simple kriging is that it assumes that all the data points are a residual from a constant mean across the area. This could give us a biased estimate, especially if there are differences in data density at different elevations. Let's try ordinary kriging, where the mean is unknown.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d62f2d94-dd7b-4dd6-bfd4-ec8f14e2d46a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Ordinary kriging\n",
    "Ordinary kriging (OK) uses a locally varying mean. This makes OK more robust to trends."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
