    "       vmin=-80, vmax=20, clabel='Difference [m]')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ede65b89-1ff8-451a-ae23-38cf8e97fc6e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The differences tend to be the most pronounced in areas that are not near conditioning points."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d346e00f-011c-4467-8973-4fed156987a6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Kriging roughness\n",
    "You'll also notice that parts of kriging outputs look quite smooth. This is because kriging performs interpolations by averaging measurements. Let's compare the variograms of the data and the kriging results to see how they differ.\n",
    "\n",
    "Notice that we're using the simple kriging values prior to back transfo.rmation because the experimental variogram was computed on normalized data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e3b040a8-c4eb-460c-803c-d66395f1a95f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# compute simple kriging variogram\n",
    "coords_s = Pred_grid_xy\n",
    "values_s = est_SK\n",
    "\n",
    "VS = skg.Variogram(coords_s, values_s, bin_func='even', n_lags=n_lags, \n",
    "                   maxlag=maxlag, normalize=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "620510c6-e7fd-474e-8732-5da4acbdddac",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# experimental variogram (from beginning of script)\n",
    "xe = V1.bins\n",
    "ye = V1.experimental\n",
    "\n",
    "# simple kriging variogram\n",
    "xs = VS.bins\n",
    "ys = VS.experimental\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n",
    "plt.plot(xe,ye,'og', markersize=4, label='Bed data variogram')\n",
    "plt.plot(xs,ys,'ob', markersize=4, label='Simple kriging variogram')\n",
    "plt.title('Variogram comparison')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Lag [m]'); plt.ylabel('Semivariance')  \n",
    "plt.legend(loc='upper left')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
